1. SBF has been put in solitary confinement after being interviewed by Tucker Carlson without permission;
2. Angola has recently cracked down on several cases of cryptocurrency "mining" involving Chinese citizens;
3. US CFTC: As of the week of March 4, the net long position of Bitcoin was 614 contracts;
4. Yesterday, Fidelity FBTC had a net outflow of US$154.9 million, and Grayscale GBTC had a net outflow of US$36.5 million;
5. Analyst: Whales bought more than 30,000 BTC in the past two weeks;
6. A giant whale released 36,156 SOLs that had been pledged for one year, making a profit of US$1.51 million;
7. Bitcoin mining company CleanSpark has been included in the S&P SmallCap 600 index;
8. Three directors of the Avalanche Foundation collectively resigned.
